Standard Operating Procedures (SOP) for WordPress Task Categorization & Time Estimation
1. Theme Customization
Layout Adjustments
Simple: Minor layout adjustments (e.g., moving sections, adjusting margins/padding, fixing section layouts) – 30 to 45 minutes.
Moderate: Rearranging elements across several pages or modifying template structures – 1 to 2 hours.
Complex: Redesigning core elements across multiple pages or significant reworking of layouts – 3 to 6 hours.
Styling & CSS
Simple: Adjusting individual element styles like colors, fonts, or padding – up to 30 minutes.
Moderate: Applying consistent styling changes across multiple sections or templates – up to 2 hours.
Complex: Reworking entire theme styles, ensuring full responsiveness – up to 4 hours.
Header & Footer Customization
Simple: Changing logos, text, or basic links – up to 30 minutes.
Moderate: Adding/removing elements like menus or widgets – up to 45 minutes.
Complex: Creating fully custom headers/footers with dynamic content – 3 to 4 hours.
Template Creation
Simple: Duplicating or modifying an existing template for a single post/page – up to 1 hour.
Moderate: Developing new templates for custom post types or archives – 3 to 6 hours.
Complex: Advanced template work involving dynamic content or conditional logic – 4 to 7 hours.
Theme Installation & Setup
Simple: Installing a theme and performing quick setup – 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Moderate: Configuring theme options, settings, and light content setup – 2 to 3 hours.
Complex: Full theme configuration, demo content setup, and functionality testing – 4 to 6 hours.

2. Functionality Customization
Plugin Customization
Simple: Minor plugin tweaks (e.g., adding a setting, changing small behaviors) – 45 minutes to 2 hours.
Moderate: Customizing multiple settings or adding custom code – 2 to 4 hours.
Complex: Advanced plugin customizations or integrating new functionality – 10 to 18 hours.
Custom Shortcodes
Simple: Creating a basic shortcode for reusable content – 45 minutes to 2 hours.
Moderate: Shortcodes with dynamic content, such as pulling from custom fields – 3 to 4 hours.
Complex: Advanced shortcodes involving APIs or dynamic data – 8 to 12 hours.
Custom Widgets
Simple: Developing a basic static widget – 1 to 2 hours.
Moderate: Widgets with dynamic content (e.g., recent posts or filtered data) – 3 to 5 hours.
Complex: Widgets with custom options or external integrations – 8 to 12 hours.
Custom Post Types & Taxonomies
Simple: Creating basic custom post types or taxonomies – 1 to 2 hours.
Moderate: Custom post types with associated templates and taxonomies – 4 to 6 hours.
Complex: Advanced custom post types with complex taxonomies and templates – 8 to 12 hours.
WooCommerce Customization
Simple: Minor WooCommerce adjustments, such as product layout changes – 1 to 2 hours.
Moderate: Customizing checkout/cart pages – 3 to 5 hours.
Complex: Advanced WooCommerce features or custom development – 10 to 12 hours.

3. Performance Optimization
Speed Optimization
Simple: Basic optimization tasks like image compression and caching setup – 45 minutes to 1.5 hours.
Moderate: Minifying CSS/JS, basic CDN setup – 2 to 4 hours.
Complex: In-depth optimizations, such as server-side caching or database cleanup – 6 to 10 hours.
Security Enhancements
Simple: Installing and configuring security plugins – 1 to 2 hours.
Moderate: Implementing SSL, security tweaks, or setting up firewalls – 3 to 4 hours.
Complex: Full security audits or fixing vulnerabilities – 6 to 10 hours.
SEO Optimization
Simple: Adding metadata, alt tags, and basic on-page SEO adjustments – 1 to 2 hours.
Moderate: Implementing schema markup and structured data – 3 to 5 hours.
Complex: Full site SEO audit, keyword analysis, and improvements – 8 to 12 hours.

4. API Integration & Backend Development
Third-Party API Integration
Simple: Connecting a basic API (e.g., Mailchimp, Google Analytics) – up to 45 minutes.
Moderate: Integrating APIs with additional logic (e.g., payments, CRM) – up to 3 hours.
Complex: Advanced API integrations with custom workflows or multiple endpoints – 5 to 10 hours.
Custom PHP Development
Simple: Small PHP scripts or minor customizations – 1 to 2 hours.
Moderate: Custom logic or workflows involving PHP – 3 to 4 hours.
Complex: Extensive backend functionality, custom logic, and database integration – 10 to 15 hours.
Database Management
Simple: Setting up basic databases or optimizing queries – 1 to 2 hours.
Moderate: Handling complex queries or managing database relationships – 3 to 5 hours.
Complex: Full database redesign or large-scale optimization – 8 to 12 hours.

5. Content Management
Content Layout & Structuring
Simple: Adding or formatting content using page builders – 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Moderate: Structuring complex content layouts – 2 to 3 hours.
Complex: Custom content layouts involving dynamic content – 4 to 6 hours.
Multilingual Support
Simple: Adding translations using a plugin – 1 to 2 hours.
Moderate: Translating multiple pages with WPML or Polylang – 3 to 5 hours.
Complex: Advanced multilingual setup involving custom post types – 6 to 10 hours.
Media Management
Simple: Organizing and uploading images or videos – up to 30 minutes.
Moderate: Setting up dynamic media galleries – 2 to 3 hours.
Complex: Custom media management solutions – 4 to 6 hours.

6. Bug Fixes & Maintenance
Bug Fixing
Simple: Fixing minor display or logic issues – 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Moderate: Resolving conflicts between plugins or themes – 2 to 3 hours.
Complex: Debugging complex issues affecting site performance – up to 6 hours.
Regular Updates
Simple: Performing updates for WordPress core, themes, and plugins – 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Moderate: Checking for compatibility issues after updates – 1.5 to 3 hours.
Complex: Resolving conflicts and ensuring functionality post-updates – 4 to 6 hours.
Website Backups
Simple: Setting up and testing automated backup systems – 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Moderate: Manual backups and cloud storage integration – 1 to 2 hours.
Complex: Implementing advanced backup strategies for larger sites – 3 to 5 hours.

Notes:
All time estimates are for individual subtasks, not full project timelines.
Tasks are often divided into smaller parts to increase efficiency and reduce total time required.
Complex tasks may require multiple subtasks, each estimated separately.

